page.title: 01GENERAL REVIEW OF BLOCK
page.content: The area is predominately rural. However, the centre four portions of the block contain a Royal Armaments Depot. The Depot is the reason for the larger than usual population within the block. Both of the small housing estates primarily cater for the Depot, and one is the actual property of the Ministry of Defence. These estates only contain rented property. There only remain the farms, the school , the chapel and the church, the post office and shop, and a few private houses within the block. afforsestation is heavy for the type of area.
